com.berbils.game.Entities.ProjectileSpawners.ProjectileTypes

Class Explosion

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.berbils.game.Entities.ProjectileSpawners.ProjectileTypes.Explosion

  • public class Explosion
extends java.lang.Object
    This class creates explosion effects, applying a texture and applying knockback and damage to certain objects in range

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      private int explosionDamage
      The amount of health damage an explosion applies to objects within its radius, note - This damage is only applied once
      private float explosionDiam
      The diameter of the explosion, used to determine the size of the explosion texture and how far it can affect bodies and apply knockback/damage.
      private java.util.HashMap<com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.g2d.Sprite,java.lang.Float> explosionSpawnTime 
      private float explosionTime 
      private java.util.ArrayList<FireEngine> fireEngHitList 
      private float knockBackPower
      used to determine the amount of force applied to bodies within range of the explosion
      private float maxBlastForce
      The maximum blast force an object can experience from a single ray, this must be set to a reasonable amount to prevent objects at very low distance to the center receiving extremely high values due to the divide by distance ^ 2
      private int noOfRays
      The number of rays sent out when an explosion occurs, the higher the rays the more accurate the explosion on affecting objects in its radius.
      private SpriteHandler spriteHandler
      The SpriteHandler for the screen currently being created upon, required to draw the explosion texture
      private java.lang.String textureFilePath
      The file path to the explosion texture
      private com.badlogic.gdx.physics.box2d.World world
      The world attached to the screen, which the raycasts and sprite will be created on

      • determineFixturesWithinExplosion

        private void determineFixturesWithinExplosion(com.badlogic.gdx.math.Vector2 explosionCenter)
        A method for determining which fixtures are within range of the explosion, then if they are instanes of FireEngine knock back force will be applied scaled by the inverse square of the distance

      • applyKnockback

        private void applyKnockback(com.badlogic.gdx.math.Vector2 explosionCenter,
                            com.badlogic.gdx.math.Vector2 blastPointOfContact,
                            com.badlogic.gdx.physics.box2d.Fixture fixture)
        This method applies a linear impulse, dependent upon the knock back force and distance from the center the fixture is, at the point of contact passed
        Parameters:
        explosionCenter - The position in meters where the explosion * center is
        blastPointOfContact - The position in pixels where the ray initially collided with the fixture
        fixture - The fixture within range of the explosion and will have knockback applied to it

      • update

        public void update(float deltaTime)
        Must be called when the world is updated and is there to check how long the explosion texture has been on screen for, removing it if it has been on for longer than the explosion time
        Parameters:
        deltaTime - The time in seconds that have elapsed in world time (Excludes time taken to draw, render etc) since the last Gdx delta call.
